9:
...It's delicious, yeah... Why is it so
delicious?
16:
This is truly a momentous occasion.
Today should be made into an
official holiday!
20: Okay, let's not go THAT far.
24:
It's all because of Mary. She taught
me over and over until I got it right.
29:
Mary?
...Yes, I've heard Wilfred speak that
name before...
33: ...We need to look into this after all.
39:
They liked it, did they? That's great,
Stella!
48:
By the way, um... Nate? What's this
on the table here?
52:
A recon drone. Knowing what we're
up against is half the battle.
57:
That's right. Let the meeting for
Operation: Snag the Childhood
Friend begin!
62:
Wilfred Mishti, a student enrolled in
the Arcane Arts Academy.
65:
He has exceptional grades and is
well-liked by his instructors.
However, he struggles to make
friends with his peers.
67:
He's treated as an outcast. Not
surprising, considering he stays
holed up in his laboratory for days,
inventing various strange devices.
71:
H-he invents all kinds of amazing
things, though. He made this thing
here when he was ten years old!
78:
Oh? You've been cherishing it all
these years, then.
83:
Th-that's not what I was getting at!
My point is that Will is always
inventing things for other people!
87:
Look! I bet Will made all those sheep,
too!
90:
I'm pretty sure I heard those things
came from a cryptic artifact they
found in the Kaleidoscope. They've
been causing a lot of trouble for the
Guild...
94:
Right, right. Will wouldn't cause
problems for people like that, would
he? He's such a kind and wonderful
person!
97:
Are you a PR bot or something?
Normal people aren't this positive
about anybody.
101:
It's true, though! Just look at him,
he's always doing his best to help
others! It's so attractive...
103:
And his sweet little smile is just the
cutest! Everything about him is cute,
really...
106:
His soft and fluffy hair, that smart
little outfit, those square glasses...
He's the very avatar of cuteness!
110: He could probably ditch the glasses—
136:
N-nobody looks better in them than
Will, though!
140:
Mary, why don't you just tell Will
what you just told us? That would do
it, for sure!
150:
W-well, uh... Describing a person
and confessing to someone are two
totally different things, you know...
153:
Oh? I'm sure he doesn't ONLY think of
you as a friend, though.
161:
B-but that's not the problem! It's just
that I keep messing up whenever I
get a chance to tell him!
167:
I'll think the moment is just right, and
then someone else suddenly shows
up, or...
171:
Or I forget my notes so I don't
remember what to say!
175:
I just... I can't find a time where the
moment's right, that's all! We've just
been friends for so many years, you
know?
181:
I see. You want to tell him when
things feel romantic enough, right?
183:
How about telling him on the water,
then? Like, a dinner cruise or
something? We could charter the
ship so nobody else gets in the way.
188:
H-huh? No, that's okay! If anything
that would just make me more
nervous!
192:
Perhaps you'd prefer something a
little simpler? Then I'll have my
people mobilize and they'll clear
everyone out of an area nearby.
Would half a day be good enough?
197:
M-mobilize? Is there something
you're not telling me about who you
are, Reticia?!
201:
Wouldn't it be a little ominous if
there weren't ANY other people
around?
206:
Would it? Well, what sort of situation
would work best for you, Mary?
210:
I guess... I'd prefer to be alone
together in a romantic way, but
make it casual enough so it's not too
nerve-wracking?
222:
H-huh?! Did that machine do this,
too? Or are you some kind of mage,
Nate?
228:
It's VR. We can easily set up any sort
of scenario we want here.
233:
Isn't this a little too... cheap? I think
the real thing would be better.
236:
Taking them to the real deal is
whole 'nother heap of trouble.
Besides, don't you think Will would
prefer this sort of thing?
240:
Y-yeah, maybe! He's interested in
technology like this!
244:
Hey, Nate! If you can set up any sort
of scenario in here, how about, um...
247: Can we... go to the beach?
252:
Good idea. This area's landlocked,
so the beach would definitely feel
pretty special. And it won't be as
nerve-wracking as a cruise ship,
either!
255:
Y-yeah. Walking together next to the
water under a bright-blue sky...
257:
Oh, but maybe the evening would
be better? We could play in the
water during the day before sitting
on the sand to watch the sunset...
260:
That's a lot more requests than I was
expecting!
264:
And then we find ourselves holding
hands before we stare at one
another, the distance closing... And
then—
267: You've got to do that part yourself!
271:
...Yeah, you're right. And with you all
cheering me on, I know I can do it!
274: I... I can finally tell him!
278: We're behind you all the way.
285:
Let Operation: Snag the Childhood
Friend begin!
